()1️⃣ URL banana:-
URL url = new URL("https://tenant.api.identitynow.com/v3/access-profiles");
Kya hai?
URL = Java class jo web address ko represent karti hai.

Yaha kya ho raha hai
https://tenant.api.identitynow.com/v3/access-profiles

Iska matlab:-
IdentityNow server ko request bhejni hai
endpoint = access-profiles
method = create access profile

()2️⃣ Connection open karna:-
HttpURLConnection conn = (HttpURLConnection) url.openConnection();
Kya hai?
HttpURLConnection = Java class jo HTTP request bhejne ke liye use hoti hai

Yaha kya ho raha hai?
Java program
      ↓
Internet connection open
      ↓
IdentityNow API server

url.openConnection()
→ server se connection open karta hai.

()3️⃣ HTTP Method set karna:-
conn.setRequestMethod("POST");
Kya hai?
HTTP methods:-
GET → data read
POST → data create
PUT → data update
DELETE → data delete
Yaha
POST = new Access Profile create

()4️⃣ Header set karna:-
conn.setRequestProperty("Authorization", "Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN");
Kya hai?
Authorization header server ko batata hai:

kaun request bhej raha hai?
Format:-
Bearer TOKEN

Example:-
Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9
Server verify karta hai.

()5️⃣ Content type:-
conn.setRequestProperty("Content-Type", "application/json");
Matlab:-
Server ko bata rahe ho:-
data JSON format me aa raha hai
Example JSON:-
{
"name":"SAP Finance Access"
}

()9️⃣ Flush:-
os.flush();
Matlab:-
Buffer me jo data hai usko forcefully server ko send karo

()1️⃣1️⃣ Response print karna:-
String line;

while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {
    System.out.println(line);
}
Kya ho raha hai?
Server response line by line read ho raha hai.

Example output:-
{
"id":"12345",
"name":"SAP Finance Access"
}
Console me print hoga.

1️⃣2️⃣ Response Code
conn.getResponseCode();
Kya hai

Server ka status code

Code	Meaning
200	   Success
201	   Created
400	   Bad request
401	   Unauthorized
500	   Server error

()1️⃣3️⃣ Connection close:-
conn.disconnect();
Matlab:-
Server connection close
resources free

()1️⃣ BufferedReader:-
BufferedReader Kya hai?
Java ki class hai (java.io package).
Kya karta hai?
Text ko line by line read karta hai

()1️⃣ conn.setDoOutput(true);
conn.setDoOutput(true);:-
setDoOutput():-
HttpURLConnection ka method hai.
Ye batata hai ki request body bhejni hai ya nahi.
Agar:-
false → data send nahi hoga
true → data send hoga

()2️⃣ OutputStream os = conn.getOutputStream();:-
OutputStream os = conn.getOutputStream();

()OutputStream:-
Java ki class (java.io)
Data ko bahar bhejne ka stream,
OutputStream → program se server ko data bhejne ka pipe.

()getOutputStream():-
Method of HttpURLConnection.
Kya karta hai?
request body bhejne ke liye stream deta hai.

3️⃣ os.write(jsonInput.getBytes());:-

()write() OutputStream ka method hai.
Kaam:-
data ko stream me bhejna.

()getBytes():-
String ka method.
Kya karta hai?
String → bytes converrt karta hai,
Kyuki network me data bytes form me send hota hai.

Example:-
"Hello"
↓
[72,101,108,108,111]

()BufferedReader br =new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(conn.getInputStream()));:-
--
BufferedReader(...):-
Yaha BufferedReader object create ho raha hai memory me.
Lekin isko ek Reader object chahiye jisse data read kare.
Isliye hum InputStreamReader pass kar rahe hain.

3️⃣ new InputStreamReader(
new InputStreamReader(
InputStreamReader
Java class (java.io).
Kaam:-
bytes → characters me convert karta hai,
Kyuki network me data bytes form me aata hai.

()getInputStream():-
Ye HttpURLConnection ka method hai.
Kaam:-
server ka response stream return karta hai
Example:-
Server response:-
{
"id":"12345",
"name":"SAP Finance Access"
}
Ye response InputStream me aata hai.
